---
title: Soy-Cumin Chicken & Hand-Pulled Noodles Supercharge your skills with this advanced recipe!
description: If you’re ready for a spicy-savory Chinese-inspired meal AND you’re ready to learn to pull your own noodles, then this recipe is for you! This dish is inspired by the biang biang noodles of Shaanxi province in Northwestern China that get their name from the sound they make when smacking the dough on the counter to stretch them out. After a quick boil, you’ll toss those homemade noodles with stir-fried soy-cumin chicken thighs, tender bell pepper and onion, a sweet soy glaze, and a sprinkle each of spicy Korean chili flakes and zippy scallion greens. Serve them family-style with a tangy-crisp cucumber salad—the perfect complement!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65c28769606e44bed2538639-0b8e5ac4.jpeg
